5|$|Greater <b>Fort</b> <b>Lauderdale,</b> {{encompassing}} all of Broward County, hosted 12 {{million visitors}} in 2012, including 2.8 million international visitors. In 2012, the county collected $43.9 {{million from the}} 5% hotel tax it charges, after hotels in the area recorded an occupancy rate for the year of 72.7 percent and an average daily rate of $114.48. The district has 561 hotels and motels comprising nearly 35,000 rooms. Forty-six cruise ships sailed from Port Everglades in 2012. Greater <b>Fort</b> <b>Lauderdale</b> has over 4,000 restaurants, 63 golf courses, 12 shopping malls, 16 museums, 132 nightclubs, 278 parkland campsites, and 100 marinas housing 45,000 resident yachts.|$|E
